-----

[[include component:image-block name=treeIII.png|align=center|width=100%|caption=SCP-6664 prior to containment.]]

-----

**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-6664 is to be contained in a greenhouse at ##blue|Site-87##. SCP-6664 is not to be climbed, for fear of damaging its branches.

**Description:** SCP-6664 is a tree of the species //##blue|Malus domestica##//, more commonly known as the ##blue|apple tree##, currently located at ##blue|Site-87##. SCP-6664 is identical to other trees of its species, save for its anomalous effects.

SCP-6664's anomalous effects activate whenever it is ##blue|approached## by ##blue|Dr. King##. When ##blue|Dr. King is positioned under the canopy of## SCP-6664, instead of ##blue|no effects## as expected, ##blue|all fruit on SCP-6664 will simultaneously disappear. All seeds contained within the fruit will fall to the ground. These seeds have## been designated SCP-6664-1.

SCP-6664-1 ##blue|are motile apple seeds produced by SCP-6664##. SCP-6664-1 ##blue|are capable of manipulating where they land, universally using this to make contact with Dr. King upon falling.##

-----

[[=]]
+ **Addendum 6664.01: Discovery**
[[/=]]

SCP-6664 was discovered on January 28, 2014, after ##blue|Everett King##, a ##blue|Foundation senior researcher##, reported ##blue|walking under SCP-6664, and being pelted by several apple seeds. After walking under SCP-6664 again a few days later, he was once again hit by several instances of## SCP-6664-1 and reported it as a possible anomaly. SCP-6664 was subsequently moved to ##blue|Site-87##.

